  "prompt": "Which is the best book of maths for preparation of iit - jee?",
  "response": "The choice of the best book for IIT-JEE mathematics preparation can be subjective and often depends on individual strengths and preferences. However, several books are highly recommended by educators and successful candidates:\n\n1. **\"IIT Mathematics\" by M.L. Khanna**: This book is comprehensive and covers a wide range of problems that are crucial for IIT-JEE preparation.\n\n2. **\"Objective Mathematics\" by R.D. Sharma**: It is well-known for its clear explanations and ample practice problems that mirror the types of questions asked in the IIT-JEE.\n\n3. **\"Problems in Calculus of One Variable\" by I.A. Maron**: Widely regarded for its solid problems and thorough treatment of calculus, which is a significant part of the IIT-JEE syllabus.\n\n4. **\"Higher Algebra\" by Hall and Knight**: This classic book is excellent for understanding algebraic concepts and improving problem-solving skills.\n\n5. **\"Trigonometry\" by S.L. Loney**: Known for its clarity and depth in trigonometry, it is a must-have for mastering this area.\n\n6. **\"Course in Mathematics for IIT-JEE\" by Tata McGraw Hill**: This series covers a broad spectrum of topics and is known for its challenging problems and clear explanations.\n\nEach of these books has its strengths, and many students find that using a combination of these resources yields the best results in their preparation. Make sure to practice regularly and understand the concepts thoroughly to excel in IIT-JEE mathematics.",
